# pyenv
#   For a library or binary, you wish to ignore these files
#   For a specific project, it may be better to check them in
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if having platform-specific dependencies or dependencies
#   having no cross-platform support, pipenv may install dependencies that don't work, or even
#   fail to install. In that case, un-commenting the following line is a duplicate of
#   Environment/Virtualenv, but it addresses a specific concern.
# Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipenv, see https://python-poetry.org/docs/basic-usage/#commit-your-poetrylock-file-to-version-control
# poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipenv, see https://pdm.fming.dev/#use-pdm-in-a-project
.pdm-python
.pdm-build/

